re resolves its required Kotlin reflection/coroutines dependencies transitively, and meaningful core coverage is reachable with built-in MapPropertySource, Props/.properties parsing, decoders, preprocessors, and classpath/resource APIs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Hoplite documentation examples often use YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON; those formats require optional hoplite-yaml, hoplite-json, hoplite-toml, or hoplite-hocon modules and should not be assumed available when testing hoplite-core alone.\",\n    \"Hoplite 3 applies environment variables as a default property source, so tests should prefer explicit builder setup or map/props sources when they need deterministic input.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e8de180a689063d016a42601ebe6c8193bb0cc31cacda32c4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1836, "output": 702, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39402, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782734868209, "responseId": "resp_0e8de180a689063d016a426014d680819390b4f4fbe66980e9"}}
